    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im working on my 2018 camry and just finished replacing the brake pads. but now when i take it out on the road i hear this really annoying high pitched squealing sound whenever i hit the brakes. not sure if its a sensor or if the caliper might be stuck or something. any idea what thats could be?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That high-pitched squeal after replacing pads is a common issue with a few potential causes. It could be due to improperly bedded new pads, a slight contamination on the rotor or pads, or sometimes the anti-rattle clips aren't seated correctly. If the noise is consistent and irritating, you might want to check if the calipers are centered or if there's any excessive vibration when braking. Getting a mechanic to inspect the rotor surface and pad shims is usually the best next step.",
      "source": "target",
