      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the clips and they seem fine. the squeal is really sharp though, almost like a metal-on-metal screeching sound. i tried to see if it was just the sensor chirping but it feels more constant than that. do you think i should pull the wheel back off and check the caliper piston? i dont want to mess up the new pads if it's something else.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since you're hearing a sharp, almost metallic screech, it sounds more serious than just a simple sensor chirp. Before diving into the piston, you could try a quick test by lightly spraying some brake cleaner on the pad contact points and driving gently to try and \"bed\" the new pads in. If the screech persists after a short bedding-in period, carefully inspecting the caliper piston for any signs of sticking or seizing would be wise. If the piston is binding, the pads won't seat properly, causing that harsh noise.",
      "source": "target",
