    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried the bedding thing but it didnt really help, the noise is still there and it's driving me crazy. it's such a weird, piercing sound. it's almost like its coming from deep inside the wheel assembly, almost like some kind of high pitched whistle or scream. i've checked everything else but i can't find the source. is there any other part of the assembly that could cause a sound that aggressive?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched, piercing whistle from the wheel assembly, especially after new pads, could point toward a few less common issues. Sometimes, a slight vibration or chatter in the caliper bracket itself can resonate at a very high frequency. Another possibility is a very minor issue with the rotor's runout or a thin piece of debris lodged between the pad and rotor. If simple cleaning and bedding didn't work, it might be time to have a professional check the caliper mounting bolts and rotor surface for imperfections.",
      "source": "target",
